<emphasis box="[499,704,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pistacia lentiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. in woods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,746,1932]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,268,1706,1732]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1908" box="[282,492,1707,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Peritelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inviridis">
<emphasis box="[282,492,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Peritelus inviridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Solari, A. &amp; Solari, F." box="[722,983,1706,1732]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="54 - 60" refId="ref47251" refString="Solari, A. &amp; Solari, F. (1922) Alcune note sui Peritelus e specialmente su quelli appartenenti al sottogenere Homorhythmus Bedel. Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 54 (4), 54 - 60." type="journal article" year="1922">Solari &amp; Solari (1922)</bibRefCitation>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schaufuss, 1882" authorityName="Schaufuss" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Peritelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuicornis">
<emphasis box="[1188,1348,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. tenuicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schaufuss, L. W." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="527 - 552" refId="ref46900" refString="Schaufuss, L. W. (1882) Zoologische Ergebnisse von Excursionen auf den Balearen. III (Addenda und Fortsetzung). Numquam Otiosus, 3, 527 - 552." type="journal article" year="1882">Schaufuss, 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the elytral profile “ 
<emphasis box="[633,1137,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">ex humeris ad posticam partem angustatis</emphasis>
” — according to Schaufuss’ description —, a character in fact shared by different 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1863" box="[875,986,1786,1812]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Peritelini">Peritelini</taxonomicName>
. Examination of Pic’s 
<typeStatus box="[1264,1314,1786,1812]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
specimen revealed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaufuss" authorityYear="1882" box="[309,470,1827,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Peritelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuicornis">
<emphasis box="[309,470,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. tenuicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is actually easy to distiguish, apart from the characters in the key also by the indicated longitudinal keel on the pronotum, the suberect elytral setae and the pre-apical region of aedeagus being bent down and broadened.
</paragraph>
